comments.text: My childhood Hero! The Football player of Dreams! Tall, Classy, Elegant and so Fast! Oh that mythical speed! One of the biggest mysteries in the history of Football - how can a player with his physique (186 cm) run at 35 km/h on the field?!? MADNESS!!! PURE NATURAL TALENT! Absurd acceleration! Legendary Pace! UNSTOPPABLE!!! He was not the typical dribbler like Maradona and Pele who are short and bombard the field with feints and tricks. Ricardo never liked to apply feints (unless it was necessary). He used his brain capacity to the maximum! His movements, his passes, his finishing kicks were simple and elegant. He made football look easy. Ricardo Kaká is the most accomplished Attacking Midfielder of his generation and one of the greatest human beings to ever play Football. One of the last Romantics on the field from the last years when this game was still beautiful. I wish today's "stars" were like him, but that's impossible! Lionel Messi, Cristiano Ronaldo, Mohamed Salah, Killian Mbape, etc. etc. etc. they have no charisma ...no aura because they play for money and fame and not out of love for this beautiful game called Football. No matter how many Ballon d'Or they win, no matter how many records they break, no matter how many goals they score, they will never even come close to Ricardo Kaká and his generation. "I belong to Jesus" - Ricardo Kaká
